<span class="gutter">  24:</span>  <span class="syntax17">&lt;</span><span class="syntax17">hr</span><span class="syntax17">&gt;</span>
<span class="gutterH">  25:</span> <span class="syntax17">&lt;</span><span class="syntax17">/</span><span class="syntax17">body</span><span class="syntax17">&gt;</span>
<span class="gutter">  26:</span><span class="syntax17">&lt;</span><span class="syntax17">/</span><span class="syntax17">html</span><span class="syntax17">&gt;</span></span>
</PRE>
</div>
</small></blockquote>
<p>
After the user has filled out the form and pressed the Submit button, the action
in the &lt;form&gt; tag's action attribute is triggered, sending the data to the
server and then to the PHP program listed in the URL.
</p><p>
The superglobal $_REQUEST array receives the form data.
</p>
<h4>
Filename: request.php (The PHP Script)
</h4>
<blockquote><small>
<div class="disp2">
